        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 19 at 8:52AM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 852 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Widener, or near Madison, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Forrest City, Hughes, Madison, Village Creek State Park, Widener,
Jennette, New Home, Cottonwood Corner, Jonquil, Tarsus, Round Pond,
Blackfish, Democrat, Kinton, North Hughes, Hicks Station, Lucerne,
Whitmore, Chatfield, and Penjur.

This includes Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 243 and
264.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
